Race.SpecificTitle: Town of Livingston Prop. No. 1 of 5 -- Wet/Dry-6%PkgAlcoh. - M&BOA
Race.SummaryText: Town of Livingston Proposition No. 1 of 5
Race.FullText: Shall the sale of beverages of alcoholic content containing not more than six percent alcohol by volume be permitted by package only and not for consumption on the premises in the Town of Livingston?

Race.SpecificTitle: Fire Protection District No. 9 -- $32 Service Charge Renewal - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Fire Protection District No. 9 Proposition
(Service Charge Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall Fire Protection District No. 9 of the Parish of Livingston, State of Louisiana (the "District"), be authorized to renew an annual service charge of not to exceed Thirty-Two Dollars ($32.00) (an estimated $72,000.00 is reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the service charge for an entire year) from persons owning residential or commercial structures, whether occupied or unoccupied, located wholly or partly within the boundaries of the District, for a period of ten (10) years beginning with the year 2021 and ending with the year 2030, for the purpose of paying the costs of fire protection services in and for the District and assessing and collecting said service charge, owners shall be assessed a service charge for each such structure which they own, each residential or commercial unit and each housing unit within a multiple dwelling structure shall be considered a separate structure and a mobile home, as defined in R.S. 9:1149.2(3), shall be considered a structure?

Race.SpecificTitle: Fire Protection District No. 11 -- $32 Service Charge Renewal - BOC - 10 Yrs.
Race.SummaryText:
Fire Protection District No. 11 Proposition
(Service Charge Renewal)
Race.FullText: Shall Fire Protection District No. 11 of the Parish of Livingston, State of Louisiana (the "District") be authorized to renew an annual service charge of not to exceed Thirty-Two Dollars ($32.00) from persons owning residential or commercial structures, whether occupied or unoccupied, located wholly or partly within the boundaries of the District, (an estimated $12,500.00 is reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the service charge for an entire year), for a period of ten (10) years beginning with the year 2021 and ending the year 2030, for the purpose of paying the costs of fire protection services in and for the District, and for purposes of assessing and collecting said service charge, owners shall be assessed a service charge for each such structure which they own, each residential or commercial unit and each housing unit within a multiple dwelling structure shall be considered a separate structure and a mobile home, as defined in R.S. 9:1149.2(3)?
